#####
Way A
#####

1. Start the game.

2. Begin a NEW GAME or LOAD A SAVED GAME.

3. Enable DEBUG MODE:
   Press and Hold all three of these keys "Alt Ctrl Shift".
   Now keep holding those keys my son, & hit "D".  Release all of the keys!
   There is no notice that debug mode is enabled, but it SHOULD be.

4. Open the game Console:
   Hit the key " ` " or " ~ " also known as Tilde.
   A CONSOLE window should open with a cursor.

5. Enter your codes.

6. Hit " ` " or " ~ " to leave the console.

7. You can toggle DEBUG MODE back to disabled with Alt-Ctrl-Shift-D!


#####
Way B
#####

1. Always make a backup copy of your game file(s):
   DynamicResources\Config\autoexec.con
   DynamicResources\Config\Default.ksb

2. UnRAR the archive to your game directory, overwriting any existing files.
   Always unRAR with full paths!

3. Start the game.

4. The above steps enabled in-game Hot Keys (as coded by the game developers) 
   to various cheats functions.
   TNT has re-binded the DEBUG MODE toggler to Ctrl-D because on our keyboards, 
   the lame 4-key combo does not fucking WORK!!!!!!

5. From the Main Menu, go to:
   Options -> Controls -> Define Keys -> Shortcut_ToggleDebugCommands
   You can change DEBUG MODE toggler if you wish.
   Also, note the following sections:
     Shortcut_Debug
     Shortcut_Cheat
   Both the Debug binds and Cheat binds give cheat like functions.
   Feel free to change the hot keys.
   * NOTE: Way "A" does NOT enable the Shortcut_Debug/Cheat key definers.

6. Begin a NEW GAME or LOAD A SAVED GAME.

7. Enable DEBUG MODE:
   Press and Hold "Ctrl" and "D".
   Release all of the keys!
   There is no notice that debug mode is enabled, but it SHOULD be.

